From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lucas Sampaio <lucas@tigera.io>
Date: Thu, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix informer GVR plural strings

Upstream k8s 1.36 informer-gen hardcodes the resource name on the new
WithInformerName(gvr) call as `strings.ToLower(typeName) + "s"` (see
code-generator/cmd/informer-gen/generators/informer.go), inconsistent
with the same generator's generic.go output which uses
NewAllLowercasePluralNamer with --plural-exceptions. The result is that
7 of Calico's v3 types get a GVR.Resource string that doesn't match the
real API plural and therefore won't correlate with apiserver-side
metrics when callers opt into cache.NewInformerName(...).

No functional impact (List/Watch goes through the typed clientset
method, which has the correct plural in the URL), but the wrong string
surfaces as a label on reflector metrics and trace fields. Rewrite the
seven GVR.Resource strings to the real API plural.

Remove this patch when upstream informer-gen is fixed; `patch -p2` will
fail to apply once the buggy strings are gone and signal that this
file can be deleted.
---
 .../externalversions/projectcalico/v3/blockaffinity.go              | 2 +-
 .../externalversions/projectcalico/v3/caliconodestatus.go           | 2 +-
 .../externalversions/projectcalico/v3/globalnetworkpolicy.go        | 2 +-
 .../externalversions/projectcalico/v3/networkpolicy.go              | 2 +-
 .../externalversions/projectcalico/v3/stagedglobalnetworkpolicy.go  | 2 +-
 .../projectcalico/v3/stagedkubernetesnetworkpolicy.go               | 2 +-
 .../externalversions/projectcalico/v3/stagednetworkpolicy.go        | 2 +-
 7 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

